India Regulator Asked NSE to Cut Ncdex Stake to 5% by Sept. 30

-- B y   S w a n s y   A f o n s o
-- 
2011-10-17T12:40:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/india-regulator-asked-nse-to-cut-ncdex-stake-to-5-by-sept-30.html
India ’s commodity market regulator
asked the National Stock Exchange Ltd., the nation’s biggest
bourse, to reduce its stake in the National Commodity &
Derivatives Exchange Ltd. to 5 percent by Sept. 30.  The Forward Markets Commission on Sept. 27 notified the
exchange the federal government’s approval of a deadline of
Sept. 30 for completing the sale of equity in excess of 5
percent in the commodity exchange to Oman Investment Fund, the
regulator said on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Swansy Afonso in Mumbai at 
